---
/**
 * MemoryTriad — three overlapping rings labelling the cognitive-science
 * memory taxonomy that Strata's vault scopes map onto.
 *
 * Episodic ∩ Procedural = `lessons/` bridge
 * Episodic ∩ Semantic = `decisions/` (events that became facts)
 * Semantic ∩ Procedural = how-to backed by domain truths
 */
---

<figure class="triad" role="img" aria-label="Episodic, semantic, procedural memory — overlapping circles">
  <svg viewBox="0 0 520 420" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
    <defs>
      <radialGradient id="ring-fill" cx="50%" cy="50%" r="50%">
        <stop offset="0%" stop-color="var(--sl-color-accent)" stop-opacity="0.18"/>
        <stop offset="70%" stop-color="var(--sl-color-accent)" stop-opacity="0.06"/>
        <stop offset="100%" stop-color="var(--sl-color-accent)" stop-opacity="0"/>
      </radialGradient>
    </defs>

    <g class="ring-bg">
      <circle cx="180" cy="180" r="120" fill="url(#ring-fill)"/>
      <circle cx="340" cy="180" r="120" fill="url(#ring-fill)"/>
      <circle cx="260" cy="290" r="120" fill="url(#ring-fill)"/>
    </g>

    <g class="ring-stroke" fill="none" stroke="var(--sl-color-accent)" stroke-width="1.2">
      <circle cx="180" cy="180" r="120" opacity="0.7"/>
      <circle cx="340" cy="180" r="120" opacity="0.7"/>
      <circle cx="260" cy="290" r="120" opacity="0.7"/>
    </g>

    <g class="ring-labels"
       font-family="JetBrains Mono Variable, monospace"
       font-size="11"
       font-weight="600"
       letter-spacing="0.1em"
       fill="currentColor"
       paint-order="stroke"
       stroke="var(--sl-color-bg)"
       stroke-width="4">
      <text x="100" y="90"  text-anchor="start">EPISODIC</text>
      <text x="420" y="90"  text-anchor="end">SEMANTIC</text>
      <text x="260" y="395" text-anchor="middle">PROCEDURAL</text>
    </g>

    <g class="ring-sublabels"
       font-family="Inter Variable, sans-serif"
       font-size="10.5"
       fill="currentColor"
       fill-opacity="0.6"
       paint-order="stroke"
       stroke="var(--sl-color-bg)"
       stroke-width="4">
      <text x="100" y="106" text-anchor="start">pr-context/</text>
      <text x="420" y="106" text-anchor="end">domain/ · decisions/</text>
      <text x="260" y="411" text-anchor="middle">procedural/</text>
    </g>

    <g class="intersections"
       font-family="Inter Variable, sans-serif"
       font-size="10.5"
       font-style="italic"
       fill="currentColor"
       fill-opacity="0.85"
       paint-order="stroke"
       stroke="var(--sl-color-bg)"
       stroke-width="4">
      <text x="260" y="170" text-anchor="middle">decisions ← events</text>
      <text x="170" y="260" text-anchor="middle">lessons/</text>
      <text x="350" y="260" text-anchor="middle">how-to with truth</text>
    </g>

    <g class="centre-label"
       font-family="Fraunces Variable, Georgia, serif"
       font-size="13"
       font-weight="500"
       fill="var(--sl-color-accent)"
       paint-order="stroke"
       stroke="var(--sl-color-bg)"
       stroke-width="4">
      <text x="260" y="226" text-anchor="middle" letter-spacing="0.04em">vault</text>
    </g>
  </svg>
  <figcaption>
    Three memory types from the cognitive-science literature. Strata's six
    scopes sit at the rings and their overlaps, so the right retrieval
    shape is always one query away.
  </figcaption>
</figure>

<style>
  .triad {
    margin: 4rem auto 0;
    max-width: 40rem;
    text-align: center;
  }
  .triad svg {
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    color: var(--sl-color-text);
  }
  .triad figcaption {
    font-family: var(--strata-font-display);
    font-style: italic;
    font-variation-settings: 'opsz' 24;
    color: var(--sl-color-gray-2);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    line-height: 1.55;
    margin-top: 1rem;
    padding: 0 1rem;
  }

  @media (prefers-reduced-motion: no-preference) {
    .ring-bg circle,
    .ring-stroke circle {
      animation: ring-in 0.8s cubic-bezier(0.22, 0.61, 0.36, 1) backwards;
    }
    .ring-bg circle:nth-child(1), .ring-stroke circle:nth-child(1) { animation-delay: 0.05s; }
    .ring-bg circle:nth-child(2), .ring-stroke circle:nth-child(2) { animation-delay: 0.15s; }
    .ring-bg circle:nth-child(3), .ring-stroke circle:nth-child(3) { animation-delay: 0.25s; }
  }

  @keyframes ring-in {
    from { opacity: 0; transform: scale(0.94); transform-origin: center; }
    to   { opacity: 1; transform: scale(1); }
  }
</style>
